'''sysfs''' is a virtual [[filesystem]]. It exports information about devices and drivers and is also used for configuration. It's generated by the kernel and always mounted at {{Path|/sys}}.

== Usage ==
* Use '''cat''' to read the information, e.g. output the charging level of a battery:
{{Cmd|cat /sys/class/power_supply/BAT0/status}}

* To set values at runtime - if possible - use '''echo''', e.g. to enable system suspension:
{{RootCmd|echo mem > /sys/power/state}}

* To set values at boot time - if possible - create a [[local.d]] script.

